ğŸš€ Deployment Steps
1ï¸âƒ£ Create S3 Bucket

Bucket name must be globally unique

Region: any (example: ap-southeast-1)

Disable Block all public access

2ï¸âƒ£ Upload Website Files

Upload the following files to the S3 bucket:

index.html

error.html

assets/ (if any)
         
3ï¸âƒ£ Enable Static Website Hosting

Go to Bucket â†’ Properties

Enable Static website hosting

Set:

Index document: index.html

Error document: error.html
         
4ï¸âƒ£ Configure Bucket Policy

Apply a bucket policy to allow public access:

{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": "*",
      "Action": "s3:GetObject",
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::your-bucket-name/*"
    }
  ]
}


âš ï¸ Replace your-bucket-name with your actual bucket name.
         5ï¸âƒ£ Access Website

Use the Static Website Endpoint provided by Amazon S3:

http://your-bucket-name.s3-website-region.amazonaws.com

